reviews.text: Expensive hotel grade buffet that doesn't disappoint.  Food was great and staff was professional.  Roast beef was too notch.  The must try is the creme cheese tart for dessert.  Only complaint was the washroom being located outside of the restaurant and requires an access card from the front of the restaurant to access.  Poor design from the building itself.  This is however, common, for many restaurants that are in Hong Kong as building code does not require restaurants to have built in washrooms like North American countries.

Environment - cozy place. But quiet noisy maybe it’s because the floor height is not tall enough. You can feel and hear the sounds all around you.

Food - The food is quiet good, sushi are fresh and there’s a lot of seafood choices. Lobster, shrimps, etc.

Services - They hiring some of the fresh join waiters. They serve seems a bit rush and my experience is I haven’t finish the dishes yet and they already asking me can I take the dishes....Not really like this kind of service at all.
I had both buffet lunch and tea buffet here, the settings are good with different food stations people doesn't have to jam together and queue up. Good varieties.
The restaurant is very nice and the restaurant is also very modern.
Theatre kitchen my arse. The only theatre you'll get here is diners pigging themselves out with a sideshow of gross manners. It would all be entertaining except for the ridiculously expensive price.

reviews.text: This hotel has rooms with either traditional, older furniture or more modern decoration. Mostly the rooms are above average, especially for Hong Kong’s standard. Each room is also provided with a mobile phone which acts as a portable WiFi device that you can bring out to avail yourself data while walking about, which is a bonus feature I really like. The executive lounge is very impressive, with excellent staff as well as amenities.
Nice hotel. Great and convenient location. Located in the centre of Causeway Bay and next to Victoria Park. Easy to go shopping and lots of restaurants around. Nice view from the hotel rooms as well.
Breakfast.. good selection incl organic muesli! Interesting deco and good service.. enjoy
Fabulous rooms, great location, tacky coffee shop
Great location. Nice room. Very nice lounge.  Across from Victoria Park. First time I ever stayed at a Park Lane hotel during my travels, but I would consider it again.

This hotel has rooms with either traditional, older furniture or more modern decoration. Mostly the rooms are above average, especially for Hong Kong’s standard. Each room is also provided with a mobile phone which acts as a portable WiFi device that you can bring out to avail yourself data while walking about, which is a bonus feature I really like. The executive lounge is very impressive, with excellent staff as well as amenities.

홍콩의 가성비 좋은 호텔중 하나입니다. 코스웨이 베이에 위치해 이케아와 24시 슈퍼, 큰 쇼핑몰들이 호텔에서 걸어서 5-10분 거리에 포진해 있습니다. 숙박료 또한 높지도 낮지도 않고 무난합니다. 

매우 깨끗하고, 최근에 리뉴얼 한 쪽으로 방을 체크인 또는 예약하기 원한다고 미리 이야기 하면 더 좋은 룸을 얻을 수 있습니다. 

단, 매우 합리적인 비즈니스 호텔의 느낌이므로 럭셔리한 분위기를 원한다면 더 높은 가격대의 호텔을 추천드립니다. 리뉴얼한 쪽은 아직 새로운 건물 특유의 냄세가 날 수 있습니다. 

조식은 종류가 매우 다양하고 특히 딤섬이 맛있습니다. 공항행 리무진 서비스 가격 역시 합리적이로 단체로 이동할 때에는 이용해 보는 것도 좋습니다.
銅鑼湾惠康地方很大，貨物很多，本地和各國的貨物都有，價格適中，貨物新鲜。

reviews.text:
合乎期望的自助餐。 每款食物都不錯。 網上訂位八折後550蚊一個人度。

有龍蝦，即開生蠔，煎鴨肝等比較貴價的食物。 反而想講下個燉湯，真係要必飲， 飲得出個湯有心機燉咗好耐。 

本來想試過茅台味雪糕，可惜當日沒有。
